<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id748e3264-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s120109"><num value="120109">§ 120109.</num><heading> Service of process</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The corporation shall have a designated agent in the District of Columbia to receive service of process for the corporation. Notice to or service on the agent is notice to or service on the corporation.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id748e3265-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/110/254/s1/a/2">Pub. L. 110–254, § 1(a)(2)</ref>, <date date="2008-06-30">June 30, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/2421">122 Stat. 2421</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
